nndsxT3E3MIB.name: nndsxT3E3MIB
nndsxT3E3MIB.contactinfo: Nortel Networks 8200 Dixie Road Brampton, Ontario L6T 5P6 Canada 1-800-4Nortel www.nortelnetworks.com
nndsxT3E3MIB.description: Interface MIB definitions for T3/E3 interface modules.

nndsxT3E3IfConfigLineTable.name: nndsxT3E3IfConfigLineTable
nndsxT3E3IfConfigLineTable.description: A list of T3/E3 interfaces currently configured.

nndsxT3E3IfConfigLineEntry.name: nndsxT3E3IfConfigLineEntry
nndsxT3E3IfConfigLineEntry.description: An entry containing configuration information for each currently active T3/E3 interface.

nndsxT3E3IfIndex.name: nndsxT3E3IfIndex
nndsxT3E3IfIndex.description: An integer value that is an index to the entries of ifTable (MIB-II) whose interface type is ds3.

nndsxT3E3IfConfigLineType.name: nndsxT3E3IfConfigLineType
nndsxT3E3IfConfigLineType.description: This variable indicates the variety of T3/E3 C-bit or E3 application implementing this interface. The type of interface affects the interpretation of the usage and error statistics. The rate of T3/E3 is 44.736 Mbps and E3 is 34.368 Mbps. The values, in sequence, describe: linetype-m13 ANSI T1.107-1988 linetype-cbitparity ANSI T1.107a-1990

nndsxT3E3IfConfigLineCode.name: nndsxT3E3IfConfigLineCode
nndsxT3E3IfConfigLineCode.description: This variable describes the variety of zero code suppression used on this interface, which in turn affects a number of its characteristics. linecode-B3ZS and linecode-HDB3 refer to the use of specified patterns of normal bits and bipolar violations that are used to replace sequences of zero bits of a specified length.

nndsxT3E3IfConfigCableLength.name: nndsxT3E3IfConfigCableLength
nndsxT3E3IfConfigCableLength.description: The length of the T3/E3 line in feet. This object provides information for line build out circuitry if it exists and can use this object to adjust the line build out.

nndsxT3E3IfConfigTransmitClock.name: nndsxT3E3IfConfigTransmitClock
nndsxT3E3IfConfigTransmitClock.description: The source of transmit clock. It is derived from the recovered receive clock of another T3/E3 interface.

nndsxT3E3IfAlarmThresholdConfigTable.description: A list of TE3 interface alarm threshold configuration.

nndsxT3E3IfAlarmThresholdConfigEntry.description: An entry containing alarm configuration information for each currently active TE3 interface.

nndsxT3E3IfAlarmThresholdConfigIndex.name: nndsxT3E3IfAlarmThresholdConfigIndex
nndsxT3E3IfAlarmThresholdConfigIndex.description: Index value of the threshold configuration.

nndsxT3E3IfAlarmThresholdConfigObject.name: nndsxT3E3IfAlarmThresholdConfigObject
nndsxT3E3IfAlarmThresholdConfigObject.description: Configurable variables for the threshold alarm configuration.

nndsxT3E3IfAlarmThresholdConfigSamplingI.name: nndsxT3E3IfAlarmThresholdConfigSamplingInterval
nndsxT3E3IfAlarmThresholdConfigSamplingI.description: Sampling interval for the threshold alarm.

nndsxT3E3IfAlarmThresholdConfigSampleTyp.name: nndsxT3E3IfAlarmThresholdConfigSampleType
nndsxT3E3IfAlarmThresholdConfigSampleTyp.description: Sampling type for the threshold alarm.

nndsxT3E3IfAlarmThresholdConfigEnable.name: nndsxT3E3IfAlarmThresholdConfigEnable
nndsxT3E3IfAlarmThresholdConfigEnable.description: Config Enable: If TRUE then configure the threshold. FALSE then remove the threshold.

nndsxT3E3IfTestConfigType.name: nndsxT3E3IfTestConfigType
nndsxT3E3IfTestConfigType.description: Test type for the TE3 interface. Only TestType is mandatory to perform no-test, payload-loopback-test, line-loopback-test, local-loopback-test or internal-loopback-test. ConfigLoopCode is mandatory to perform remote-lpup-test and remote-lpdn-test. ConfigPattern and ConfigTime are mandatory to perform pattern test on T3. The pattern-test, payload-loopback-test, local-loopback-test and internal-loopback-test are applicable only on Clear channel T3 interface.

nndsxT3E3IfTestConfigPattern.name: nndsxT3E3IfTestConfigPattern
nndsxT3E3IfTestConfigPattern.description: Bit Pattern type used in testing T3 for Pattern Test.

nndsxT3E3IfTestConfigTime.name: nndsxT3E3IfTestConfigTime
nndsxT3E3IfTestConfigTime.description: When set to 0, test time is unlimited. Otherwise duration of test, specified in seconds.

nndsxT3E3IfStatusLineStatus.name: nndsxT3E3IfStatusLineStatus
nndsxT3E3IfStatusLineStatus.description: Line Status of the T3/E3 interface. sendPattern - TRUE if the line transmiting bit pattern, sendTE3Code - sending T3/E3 code, sendResetCode - transmits Reset Code if it is TRUE, sendPayloadcode - transmits the payload code, sendLinecode - transmitts the line code, febe - Far End Block Error, pde - pulse Density code transmission, lorc - loss of recieve clock, rfebe - recieve far end block error, ris - recieve Idle signal, rexz - recieve exessive zeros, rcvTestCode - recieve test code, loopback - loopback status , rlos - recieve loss of signal, rlof - recieve loss of frame, tais - transmit alarm indication signal, rais - recieve alarm indication signal, trai - transmit remote alarm indication, rrai - recieve remote alarm indication,

nndsxT3E3IfStatusTransmitClock.name: nndsxT3E3IfStatusTransmitClock
nndsxT3E3IfStatusTransmitClock.description: The source of tranmit clock. 'timing-line' indicates that the recovered receive clock is used as the transmit clock. 'timing-internal' indicates that a local clock source is used.

nndsxT3E3IfAlarmStatusAlarmStatus.name: nndsxT3E3IfAlarmStatusAlarmStatus
nndsxT3E3IfAlarmStatusAlarmStatus.description: Current status of all the T3/E3 interface alarms. RRAI - Recieve Remote Alarm Indication, TRAI - Transmit Remote Alarm Indication, TAIS - Transmit Alarm Indication Siganl, RLOF - Recieve Loss Of Frame, RLOS - Recieve Loss Of Sync, Loopback - Status of Loop back, rcvTestCode - Recieve Test Code, rblu - Recieve Blue Alarm, RIS - Recieve Idle Signal, REXZ - Recieve Excessive Zeros, RFBE - Recieve Frame Bit Error, RPE - Recieve Parity Error, RCPE - Recieve C-Parity Error, LORC - Loss Of Recive Clock (LORC), TPDE - transmit pulse density, RAIS - Recieve Alarm Indication Signal, TFEBE - Transmit Far End Block Alarm.
